Python Exception Handling : 
Exceptions are the runtime anomalies(unexpected situation) which may arise during the execution of program and the mechanism of handling such type of exceptions are known as Exception handling mechanism.

Exception Handling Mechanism : 
    a. Find the problem (Hit the exception)
    b. Inform that error has occured(Throw the exception)
    c. Receive the error information(Catch the exception)
    d. Take corrective measures(Handle the exception)

Keywords used in exception handling : 
    a. try
    b. except 
    c. raise 
    d. finally

Yes — in Python, exceptions are classes.

More specifically, all exceptions are objects derived from a base class called BaseException. When an error occurs, Python creates an object (instance) of an exception class and raises it.

